Paper: hep-th/9710226

Date: 1997-10-29

Title: Matrix Schwarzschild Black Holes in Large N limit

Comments: 11 pages, harvmac, references added

Journal-ref: JHEP 9801 (1998) 009

Based on a gas picture of D0-brane partons, it is shown that the entropy, aswell as the geometric size of an infinitely boosted Schwarzschild black hole,can be accounted for in matrix theory by interactions involving spins, orinteractions involving more than two bodies simultaneously.